{
  "stem": "25598.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And he had a lot of connections with non-Jews who used to bring to the hut food.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And of course, hey, it was great, because they got a coat for a little-- for a few potato.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But then eventually, we ran out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I-- I had very long hair-- long, dark, beautiful hair, which was below my waist.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And my mother used to sit and brush my hair.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And-- and soon we got lice, because there was no way of washing.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They were used to lice.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Lice was a part of their life.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "With the way I was brought up and with my mother's compulsive cleanliness, lice or bed bugs-- there weren't any beds, but there were bed bugs.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Seeing these things crawl on us was horrendous.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It was just very, very painful-- very traumatic.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And-- and-- and Tosia would sit for hours watching my mother play around with my hair and be sort of-- I-- I he was my first boyfriend, if you can call it that way.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "He was gorgeous.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "None of my boyfriends ever came to his standard in terms of beauty.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But he-- we weren't even talking.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "We were just sitting looking at each other.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Anyway, so in order to keep the lice away from my hair, my parents bartered some things for naphtha-- naphtha is some kind of a liquid fuel-- because if you washed your hair with naphtha, that kills the lice-- for a while.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "But it's very-- it's very rough on your scalp.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "It-- it burns the hell out of it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And eventually, they didn't have enough things to-- but we-- food was more important than naphtha.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "So my hair had to be cut, and that was a very big source of sorrow for me.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Because I took great pride in my hair.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
